description.narrative:
Oxfam has been working to support the participation of young people for decades, either through tailored youth programming or through supporting young women and men participating in broader community programmes. The learning that Oxfam has gained from its work inthis space has been vast. Lessons have highlighted the importance of personal empowerment, the need to work with power holders to create a supportive and enabling environment, and the crucial role that family, mentors and others in the communityplay in young people’s quest to create lasting social change. In addition to this, lessons have pointed to the importance of young people having specific roles and spaces to develop, and contributing to the development process in ways and areas that are meaningful to them, as opposed to representing ‘the voice of youth’ in predetermined priority areas. Overall Objective of the Oxfam Learning Community: To create a space which brings together Oxfam staff, partners and youth groups that have experience orinterest in fostering youth active citizenship as a development strategy, and promotes a culture of sharing, collaboration and organisational learning.
Specific Objectives: Connect: Oxfam staff, partners and youth groups who have an interest in youthactive citizenship connect with each other Share <(>&<)> Learn: Knowledge and skill sharing and learning on approaches, experience and tools enable Oxfam and partners to maximize their impact and resources Support <(>&<)> Facilitate: Collective initiatives fosteringyouth active citizenship within the confederationare facilitated; youth voice and agency within Oxfam’s broader programming and influencing agenda are increased

participating-org.narrative: Oxfam Novib was founded in 1956 as the Netherlands Organisation for International Assistance (Novib), and joined forces with Oxfam in 1994. Oxfam Novib is member of the Oxfam International confederation. Working together in the confederation, the Oxfam affiliates can speak with one clear and compelling voice on issues of global concern: climate change, health and education for all, agriculture, trade, and conflicts and emergencies. Oxfam Novib's main office is based in The Netherlands, it supports the work of a network of local offices, the implementation of global projects, fundraising, campaigning and advocacy. Oxfam Novib’s the Hague office contributes towards this project’s implementation.
